HEADWORD: Premunite
<hw>Prem`u*nite"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praemunitus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>praemunire</ets> to fortify in
front; <ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>munire</ets> to fortify.]</ety>
<def>To fortify beforehand; to guard against objection.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Fotherby.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Premunition</ent>⟦br⟧
